==English==

===Noun===

'''leash'''

#A thong of [[leather]], or a long cord, by which a [[falconer]] holds his hawk, or a [[courser]] his [[dog]].
#A brace and a half; a [[tierce]]; [[three]]; three creatures of any kind, especially [[greyhound]]s, [[fox]]es, [[buck]]s, and [[hare]]s; hence, the number three in general.
#A string with a loop at the end for lifting [[warp]] threads, in a [[loom]].
# {{surfing}} A [[leg rope]].
#: 1980: ''Probably the idea was around before that, but the first photo of the leash in action was published that year'' &mdash; ''As Years Roll By (1970's Retrospective)'', Drew Kampion, [[w:Surfing (magazine)|Surfing]] magazine, February 1980, page 43.  Quoted at surfresearch.com.au glossary[http://www.surfresearch.com.au/agl.html].

